      "start": 15.26,
      "end": 18.68,
      "text": "Recorded by Patty McCoy in Hudson, Colorado.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 21.92,
      "end": 23.2,
      "text": "Aesop's Fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 25.8,
      "end": 27.2,
      "text": "The Tunifish and the Dolphin.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 29.28,
      "end": 34.76,
      "text": "A Tunifish was chased by a dolphin and splashed through the water at a great rate.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 35.5,
      "end": 41.94,
      "text": "But the Dolphin gradually gained upon him and was just about to seize him when the force",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 41.94,
      "end": 45.84,
      "text": "of his flight carried the Tunif onto a sand rank.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 46.52,
      "end": 52.98,
      "text": "In the heat of the chase, the Dolphin followed him and there they both lay out of the water",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 52.98,
      "end": 58.54,
      "text": "gasping for dear life when the Tunif saw that his enemy was doomed like himself.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 59.7,
      "end": 62.58,
      "text": "He said, I don't mind having to die now.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 63.4,
      "end": 69.22,
      "text": "For I see that he who is the cause of my death is about to share the same fate.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 70.18,
      "end": 72.5,
      "text": "End of the Tunifish and the Dolphin.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
